{"type":"message","id":"58a88fe9","parentId":"e87ca39b","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:10:58.700Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about choosing between Mem0, LanceDB, and OpenViking. Let me think about what I know about these:\n\n1. **Mem0** - AI memory layer for LLM agents. It provides persistent memory across sessions. Has both cloud and self-hosted options. Focuses on agent memory management.\n\n2. **LanceDB** - Vector database for AI. Embeddings storage and retrieval. Works well for RAG, knowledge bases. Can be embedded (Rust-based), good for production.\n\n3. **OpenViking** - I'm not very familiar with this. Let me think... I believe this might be a newer entrant or less commonly known. \n\nI should be honest about my knowledge gaps here and do some research to give accurate comparisons rather than speculating about OpenViking's capabilities.","thinkingSignature":"52f58fb98e59a44988467af33695cf441587be2747a5a038ef04bc6d3592fa71"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n先查一下 OpenViking 的情况，再给你完整对比。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_82ddceb6fc27480a910f4a98","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"OpenViking AI memory agent 2025"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":677,"output":211,"cacheRead":27392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28280,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778033455159,"responseId":"0649d62f0a6614cd9eb16f7d80f4b691"}}
