{"type":"message","id":"27f9c948","parentId":"e542275f","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:14:58.511Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me get the OpenViking README to understand the deployment model better.","thinkingSignature":"7818566b0d60b4a09a00281fb09b144bc980c655cf43f9c8bf9d9bd2e4bb4dff"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_602c3f967a07427b9bf55cd4","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"log","sessionId":"mild-canyon"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6ec02b020c1e4384bc48f5b1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/volcengine/OpenViking/main/README.md\" 2>/dev/null | sed -n '/## Overview/,/## Quick Start/p' | head -80","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":333,"output":124,"cacheRead":36416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36873,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778033695491,"responseId":"0649d71f59906a66dead4fd0bc9fec2f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e218b25","parentId":"27f9c948","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:15:08.598Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_602c3f967a07427b9bf55cd4","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"pip install openviking --upgrade --force-reinstall\n```\n\n#### Rust CLI (Optional)\n\n```bash\ncurl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/volcengine/OpenViking/main/crates/ov_cli/install.sh | bash\n```\n\nOr build from source:\n\n```bash\ncargo install --git https://github.com/volcengine/OpenViking ov_cli\n```\n\n### 2. Model Preparation\n\nOpenViking requires the following model capabilities:\n--\n- Detect and install Ollama if needed\n- Recommend and pull suitable embedding and VLM models for your hardware\n- Generate a ready-to-use `ov.conf` configuration file\n\nTo validate your setup at any time:\n\n--\n> For cloud API providers (Volcengine, OpenAI, Gemini, etc.), continue with the manual configuration below.\n\n#### Server Configuration Template\n\nThe recommended first-time flow is:\n\n--\n> **Note**: For embedding models, supported providers are `volcengine` (Doubao), `openai`, `azure`, `jina`, `ollama`, `voyage`, `dashscope`, `minimax`, `cohere`, `vikingdb`, `gemini` (requires `pip install \"google-genai>=1.0.0\"`), `litellm`, and `local`. For VLM models, common providers include `volcengine`, `openai`, `openai-codex`, `kimi`, and `glm`.\n\n#### Server Configuration Examples\n\n👇 Expand to see the configuration example for your model service:\n\n--\npip install \"google-genai>=1.0.0\"\n```\n\n```json\n{\n  \"storage\": {\n--\npip install \"openviking[bot]\"\n\n# Option 2: Install VikingBot from source (for development)\nuv pip install -e \".[bot]\"\n\n# Start OpenViking server with Bot enabled\nopenviking-server --with-bot\n\n# In another terminal, start interactive chat\n--\nTo ensure optimal storage performance and data security, we recommend deploying on **Volcengine Elastic Compute Service (ECS)** using the **veLinux** operating system. We have prepared a detailed step-by-step guide to get you started quickly.\n\n👉 **[View: Server Deployment & ECS Setup Guide](./docs/en/getting-started/03-quickstart-server.md)**"}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"mild-canyon","total":60,"totalLines":60,"totalChars":1895,"truncated":false,"exitCode":0,"name":"curl https://raw.githubuser...nViking/main/README.md"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778033708598}}
