{"type":"message","id":"997bb67e","parentId":"dc0e2321","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:41:37.339Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_c397b88d3c23440ba92eb6a4","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"mcglothi/ai-knowledge-base | ⭐1 | Give your AI agents persistent memory — a structured Markdown knowledge base sha\njayse-office/agent-knowledge-base | ⭐0 | Shared knowledge base for OpenClaw and Claude AI agents — context, data, configs\nSalvatierraPM/knowledge-base-server | ⭐0 | Self-hosted persistent memory for AI agents. Shared brain for Claude, ChatGPT, G\ntwilson63/agents-kb | ⭐0 | Shared knowledge base for AI agents — memory, learnings, and context stored as m\nburtyuo9/rag-cloud-kb | ⭐0 | Cloud RAG Knowledge Base for AI Agent Swarm — shared memory, RL rewards, techniq"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1084,"aggregated":"mcglothi/ai-knowledge-base | ⭐1 | Give your AI agents persistent memory — a structured Markdown knowledge base sha\njayse-office/agent-knowledge-base | ⭐0 | Shared knowledge base for OpenClaw and Claude AI agents — context, data, configs\nSalvatierraPM/knowledge-base-server | ⭐0 | Self-hosted persistent memory for AI agents. Shared brain for Claude, ChatGPT, G\ntwilson63/agents-kb | ⭐0 | Shared knowledge base for AI agents — memory, learnings, and context stored as m\nburtyuo9/rag-cloud-kb | ⭐0 | Cloud RAG Knowledge Base for AI Agent Swarm — shared memory, RL rewards, techniq","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778035297339}}
{"type":"message","id":"e3296bd6","parentId":"997bb67e","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:41:40.274Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"These are very small repos. Let me search for more relevant ones specifically in the agent memory space.","thinkingSignature":"46f206b77b3ce8dc6d774a60c697d54753d87fe2a330d2121f2e027d4dc1fbab"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7a081f30d940470581d95b93","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=AI+agent+persistent+memory+vector&per_page=15&sort=stars&order=desc&topic=true\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor r in d.get('items',[])[:12]:\n    topics = ','.join(r.get('topics',[])[:4])\n    print(f\\\"{r['full_name']} | ⭐{r['stargazers_count']} | {r.get('description','N/A')[:70]}\\\")\n    if topics: print(f'  Topics: {topics}')\n    print()\n\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":311,"output":197,"cacheRead":48384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48892,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778035297345,"responseId":"0649dd614070ad5839ffa57b9b35ccf1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"48d97c93","parentId":"e3296bd6","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:41:42.541Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7a081f30d940470581d95b93","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Dataojitori/nocturne_memory | ⭐1033 | A lightweight, rollbackable, and visual Long-Term Memory Server for MC\n  Topics: agentic-ai,ai-identity,ai-memory,artificial-intelligence\n\niamtouchskyer/memex | ⭐194 | Zettelkasten-based persistent memory for AI coding agents. Works with \n  Topics: agent-memory,ai-agent,ai-coding,claude-code\n\nspences10/mcp-memory-libsql | ⭐84 | 🧠 High-performance persistent memory system for Model Context Protocol\n  Topics: ai-tools,embeddings,knowledge-graph,libsql\n\niikarus/Dragon-Brain | ⭐44 | Dragon Brain — persistent long-term memory for AI agents via MCP (Mode\n  Topics: ai-memory,claude,codex-cli,cursor\n\n28naem-del/mnemosyne | ⭐39 | Cognitive Memory OS for AI Agents — persistent, self-improving, multi-\n  Topics: agents,ai,ai-agents,artificial-intelligence\n\njoleyline/mcp-memory-libsql | ⭐24 | 🧠 High-performance persistent memory system for Model Context Protocol\n\nBluePointDigital/smart-memory | ⭐22 | A local, persistent cognitive OS for AI agents. Features continuous ba\n\nDakshC17/llm-long-term-memory-v2 | ⭐19 | A production-ready memory-enhanced AI agent that gives Large Language \n\nmindfiredigital/Agentic-Web-Starter | ⭐16 | A FastAPI-based backend scaffold for building agentic applications and\n  Topics: agent,ai,ai-agents,aiagent\n\nproject-nomos/nomos | ⭐15 | Your AI digital clone — learns who you are, acts on your behalf, remem\n  Topics: agent-memory,agent-skills,agentic-ai,ai-agents\n\nphilippjbauer/code-presents-sk-agents | ⭐12 | This repository contains the code samples and practical implementation\n  Topics: ai-agents,code-magazine,dotnet,microsoft\n\nqiuyanxin/sp-context | ⭐12 | Give every AI agent persistent memory of your team's knowledge. No vec\n  Topics: ai-agent,bm25,bun,claude-code"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2210,"aggregated":"Dataojitori/nocturne_memory | ⭐1033 | A lightweight, rollbackable, and visual Long-Term Memory Server for MC\n  Topics: agentic-ai,ai-identity,ai-memory,artificial-intelligence\n\niamtouchskyer/memex | ⭐194 | Zettelkasten-based persistent memory for AI coding agents. Works with \n  Topics: agent-memory,ai-agent,ai-coding,claude-code\n\nspences10/mcp-memory-libsql | ⭐84 | 🧠 High-performance persistent memory system for Model Context Protocol\n  Topics: ai-tools,embeddings,knowledge-graph,libsql\n\niikarus/Dragon-Brain | ⭐44 | Dragon Brain — persistent long-term memory for AI agents via MCP (Mode\n  Topics: ai-memory,claude,codex-cli,cursor\n\n28naem-del/mnemosyne | ⭐39 | Cognitive Memory OS for AI Agents — persistent, self-improving, multi-\n  Topics: agents,ai,ai-agents,artificial-intelligence\n\njoleyline/mcp-memory-libsql | ⭐24 | 🧠 High-performance persistent memory system for Model Context Protocol\n\nBluePointDigital/smart-memory | ⭐22 | A local, persistent cognitive OS for AI agents. Features continuous ba\n\nDakshC17/llm-long-term-memory-v2 | ⭐19 | A production-ready memory-enhanced AI agent that gives Large Language \n\nmindfiredigital/Agentic-Web-Starter | ⭐16 | A FastAPI-based backend scaffold for building agentic applications and\n  Topics: agent,ai,ai-agents,aiagent\n\nproject-nomos/nomos | ⭐15 | Your AI digital clone — learns who you are, acts on your behalf, remem\n  Topics: agent-memory,agent-skills,agentic-ai,ai-agents\n\nphilippjbauer/code-presents-sk-agents | ⭐12 | This repository contains the code samples and practical implementation\n  Topics: ai-agents,code-magazine,dotnet,microsoft\n\nqiuyanxin/sp-context | ⭐12 | Give every AI agent persistent memory of your team's knowledge. No vec\n  Topics: ai-agent,bm25,bun,claude-code","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778035302540}}
{"type":"message","id":"7fdea5cd","parentId":"48d97c93","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:41:45.987Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at a few interesting ones - especially \"sp-context\" which says \"Give every AI agent persistent memory of your team's knowledge. No vec\" - this is interesting. And also nocturne_memory (⭐1033) which is interesting.\n\nLet me get more details on the most relevant ones.","thinkingSignature":"970a1c678539155475753a36e5ad929ddb88656132274a1bdcf517db6741198d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b748d1a641e14ede932b8ca0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/joleyline/mcp-memory-libsql/main/README.md\" 2>/dev/null | head -80","timeout":15}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9583d0107364429f8b25e99d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/28naem/mnemosyne/main/README.md\" 2>/dev/null | head -80","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":711,"output":183,"cacheRead":48640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49534,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778035302543,"responseId":"0649dd6627eed4f3f99144990794b6c9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"448c14d1","parentId":"7fdea5cd","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:41:56.077Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b748d1a641e14ede932b8ca0","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# mcp-memory-libsql\n\nA high-performance, persistent memory system for the Model Context\nProtocol (MCP) powered by libSQL. This server provides vector search\ncapabilities and efficient knowledge storage using libSQL as the\nbacking store.\n\n<a href=\"https://glama.ai/mcp/servers/22lg4lq768\">\n  <img width=\"380\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://glama.ai/mcp/servers/22lg4lq768/badge\" alt=\"Glama badge\" />\n</a>\n\n## Features\n\n- 🚀 High-performance vector search using libSQL\n- 💾 Persistent storage of entities and relations\n- 🔍 Semantic search capabilities\n- 🔄 Knowledge graph management\n- 🌐 Compatible with local and remote libSQL databases\n- 🔒 Secure token-based authentication for remote databases\n\n## Configuration\n\nThis server is designed to be used as part of an MCP configuration.\nHere are examples for different environments:\n\n### Cline Configuration\n\nAdd this to your Cline MCP settings:\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"mcpServers\": {\n\t\t\"mcp-memory-libsql\": {\n\t\t\t\"command\": \"npx\",\n\t\t\t\"args\": [\"-y\", \"mcp-memory-libsql\"],\n\t\t\t\"env\": {\n\t\t\t\t\"LIBSQL_URL\": \"file:/path/to/your/database.db\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n### Claude Desktop with WSL Configuration\n\nFor a detailed guide on setting up this server with Claude Desktop in\nWSL, see\n[Getting MCP Server Working with Claude Desktop in WSL](https://scottspence.com/posts/getting-mcp-server-working-with-claude-desktop-in-wsl).\n\nAdd this to your Claude Desktop configuration for WSL environments:\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"mcpServers\": {\n\t\t\"mcp-memory-libsql\": {\n\t\t\t\"command\": \"wsl.exe\",\n\t\t\t\"args\": [\n\t\t\t\t\"bash\",\n\t\t\t\t\"-c\",\n\t\t\t\t\"source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh && LIBSQL_URL=file:/path/to/database.db /home/username/.nvm/versions/node/v20.12.1/bin/npx mcp-memory-libsql\"\n\t\t\t]\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n### Database Configuration\n\nThe server supports both local SQLite and remote libSQL databases\nthrough the LIBSQL_URL environment variable:\n\nFor local SQLite databases:\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"env\": {\n\t\t\"LIBSQL_URL\": \"file:/path/to/database.db\"\n\t}\n}\n```"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1079,"aggregated":"# mcp-memory-libsql\n\nA high-performance, persistent memory system for the Model Context\nProtocol (MCP) powered by libSQL. This server provides vector search\ncapabilities and efficient knowledge storage using libSQL as the\nbacking store.\n\n<a href=\"https://glama.ai/mcp/servers/22lg4lq768\">\n  <img width=\"380\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://glama.ai/mcp/servers/22lg4lq768/badge\" alt=\"Glama badge\" />\n</a>\n\n## Features\n\n- 🚀 High-performance vector search using libSQL\n- 💾 Persistent storage of entities and relations\n- 🔍 Semantic search capabilities\n- 🔄 Knowledge graph management\n- 🌐 Compatible with local and remote libSQL databases\n- 🔒 Secure token-based authentication for remote databases\n\n## Configuration\n\nThis server is designed to be used as part of an MCP configuration.\nHere are examples for different environments:\n\n### Cline Configuration\n\nAdd this to your Cline MCP settings:\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"mcpServers\": {\n\t\t\"mcp-memory-libsql\": {\n\t\t\t\"command\": \"npx\",\n\t\t\t\"args\": [\"-y\", \"mcp-memory-libsql\"],\n\t\t\t\"env\": {\n\t\t\t\t\"LIBSQL_URL\": \"file:/path/to/your/database.db\"\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n### Claude Desktop with WSL Configuration\n\nFor a detailed guide on setting up this server with Claude Desktop in\nWSL, see\n[Getting MCP Server Working with Claude Desktop in WSL](https://scottspence.com/posts/getting-mcp-server-working-with-claude-desktop-in-wsl).\n\nAdd this to your Claude Desktop configuration for WSL environments:\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"mcpServers\": {\n\t\t\"mcp-memory-libsql\": {\n\t\t\t\"command\": \"wsl.exe\",\n\t\t\t\"args\": [\n\t\t\t\t\"bash\",\n\t\t\t\t\"-c\",\n\t\t\t\t\"source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh && LIBSQL_URL=file:/path/to/database.db /home/username/.nvm/versions/node/v20.12.1/bin/npx mcp-memory-libsql\"\n\t\t\t]\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n### Database Configuration\n\nThe server supports both local SQLite and remote libSQL databases\nthrough the LIBSQL_URL environment variable:\n\nFor local SQLite databases:\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"env\": {\n\t\t\"LIBSQL_URL\": \"file:/path/to/database.db\"\n\t}\n}\n```","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778035316077}}
