{"type":"message","id":"bfb574d4","parentId":"02b53f40","timestamp":"2026-05-06T09:02:47.644Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user has two questions:\n1. Is LanceDB and OpenViking both working now? (They seem to be asking about the status of both)\n2. Can OpenViking use the same Jina API key?\n\nLet me first check the current status of the installations. The memory-lancedb-pro install seems to have had path issues. And OpenViking was already cloned in the workspace.\n\nLet me check:\n1. Is memory-lancedb-pro working?\n2. Can OpenViking use Jina API?\n\nFor OpenViking, from the docs I read earlier, it supports: `volcengine`, `openai`, `azure`, `jina`, `ollama`, `voyage`, `dashscope`, `minimax`, `cohere`, `vikingdb`, `gemini`, `litellm`, `local`. So yes, Jina is supported!\n\n\nI need to figure out what the user is actually asking. They want to know if both LanceDB and OpenViking are operational, and whether OpenViking can leverage the Jina API key that's already configured in memory-lancedb-pro.","thinkingSignature":"fd32f36a7b2e1548af632a3efb3a5e238de9187bcb2edcc8580f63e4bc7d1d5a"},{"type":"text","text":"先检查一下两边状态：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rwvjx8sjpswi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw logs --plain 2>/dev/null | grep -iE \"memory-lancedb-pro|openviking|plugin.*start|plugin.*register\" | tail -20","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":157,"output":310,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":78949,"totalTokens":79416,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778058155636,"responseId":"064a36aca6279d7b28472840abeed004"}}
