{"type":"message","id":"3670792e","parentId":"3889b477","timestamp":"2026-05-06T09:46:04.187Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to switch from Jina to MiniMax for embedding. Let me check if MiniMax supports OpenAI-compatible embedding endpoint.\n\nThe MiniMax base URL is `https://api.minimaxi.com/anthropic/v1` which uses Anthropic format, not OpenAI. But MiniMax might have a separate OpenAI-compatible endpoint for embeddings.\n\nLet me check the config and update the embedding section to use MiniMax. But first I need to verify if MiniMax supports OpenAI-compatible embedding API.\n\nActually, MiniMax does have an embedding API. Let me look at the docs. \n\nThe real problem is that their Anthropic-format endpoint won't work with memory-lancedb-pro since it expects OpenAI-compatible format. I could switch to Plan C with their existing OpenAI key for embeddings, or explore SiliconFlow or DashScope as alternatives. Let me focus on what the user actually needs: MiniMax embedding support, and either they're using their existing OpenAI key or they're willing to switch to a different provider entirely.","thinkingSignature":"cec14b8d93735472c2576dc76d62442c7d4134d2af9e33b484997d5cf221631c"},{"type":"text","text":"好，先确认一下 MiniMax 的 embedding 接口是否兼容 OpenAI 格式。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h06r7n0jl61e_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s --max-time 10 \"https://api.minimaxi.com/v1/embeddings\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer sk-cp-gtdRxxiZ_Qu_-9GM0xBF6UpeDvsYl8cPe4Y9mA-Xiy2GO8eBJSNPftqJdMb0Fl9OZAkY6sQR868fRUhTBV7OtwKyDfu-DzegI9-cDZERwbQGf3C5Wuvs38c\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"model\":\"embedding-model\",\"input\":\"hello\"}' 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":157,"output":401,"cacheRead":79960,"cacheWrite":508,"totalTokens":81026,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total"