{"type":"message","id":"718ff23c","parentId":"ecd030ed","timestamp":"2026-05-06T09:46:45.150Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now we're getting somewhere! The API is reachable and accepts the right parameters, but the account has insufficient balance. The error is `status_code: 1008, status_msg: insufficient balance`. So MiniMax embedding API works but the account doesn't have enough credits for embeddings.\n\nThis means MiniMax CAN work as an embedding provider, but the user's account needs to have sufficient balance for the embedding API specifically. The chat/LLM credits don't count toward embedding credits.\n\nSo the options are:\n1. Top up MiniMax account for embedding credits\n2. Use the OpenAI key they already have (which has 10M free tokens)\n3. Use Jina with proxy (if they have one)\n4. Use another provider\n\nGiven the context, I think the OpenAI key with free trial credits is the best option right now. Let me suggest switching to Plan C (OpenAI embedding, no reranker) using their existing free trial key.","thinkingSignature":"fec52631b6ff2b5318f23c9fe04fbb34efc91948e72b07ed8ed6afb21dd39398"},{"type":"text","text":"好消息：**MiniMax embedding API 能通**（`/v1/embeddings` 格式兼容），但账户**余额不足**。\n\n```\nstatus_code: 1008, insufficient balance\n```\n\nembedding 和 LLM 是分开计费的，你们 minimax 充值的是 LLM 额度，不是 embedding 额度。\n\n---\n\n**结论：MiniMax embedding 用不了，账户没这个额度。**\n\n---\n\n你们目前**最省钱的路**：用 OpenAI 那个 1000 万免费 token。\n\n**Plan C 配置（OpenAI embedding，不用 reranker）：**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"apiKey\": \"***\",\n    \"model\": \"text-embedding-3-small\",\n    \"baseURL\": \"https://api.openai.com/v1\"\n  },\n  \"retrieval\": {\n    \"mode\": \"hybrid\",\n    \"vectorWeight\": 0.7,\n    \"bm25Weight\": 0.3,\n    \"filterNoise\": true,\n    \"minScore\": 0.3,\n    \"hardMinScore\": 0.35\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- embedding → OpenAI free tier（10M tokens，22 个月够用）\n- Smart Extraction LLM → 你们的 minimax\n- reranker → 暂时不加\n\n要切换到这个配置吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":60938,"output":467,"cacheRead":21794,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83199,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778060793610,"responseId":"064a40f935821980c99bac56be52ca4a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"670c6ee2","parentId":"718ff23c","timestamp":"2026-05-06T09:46:55.780Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[message_id: om_x100b508490deac98b48fb63b33ccf5c]\nou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb: [Replying to: \"https://github.com/volcengine/OpenViking docker安装这个项目。可以共用jina这个api吗？\"]\n\n用这个来部署OpenViking吧，也用MiniMax的key\nReply target of current user message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"body\": \"https://github.com/volcengine/OpenViking  docker安装这个项目。可以共用jina这个api吗？\"\n}\n```"}],"timestamp":1778060815686}}
{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"user:ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b508490deac98b48fb63b33ccf5c\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"om_x100b509f4591f084c4ae8365afd546c\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-05-06 17:46 GMT+8\",\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```\n\nReply target of current user message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"body\": \"https://github.com/volcengine/OpenViking  docker安装这个项目。可以共用jina这个api吗？\"\n}\n```","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"5d2a1911","parentId":"670c6ee2","timestamp":"2026-05-06T09:46:55.793Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"b48b2977","parentId":"5d2a1911","timestamp":"2026-05-06T09:47:02.804Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to deploy OpenViking via Docker and use the Jina API (same key they already have). They're asking if it can share the same Jina API key.\n\nFrom the docs I read earlier, OpenViking supports Jina as an embedding provider and VLM model. So yes, it can use the same Jina key.\n\nLet me check the OpenViking Docker deployment docs more carefully to write the config, and confirm Jina support.","thinkingSignature":"4d0b5590cf987df85f2dbecd79cc47498576a522b7a1612a8b224b50a1784987"},{"type":"text","text":"**可以的，OpenViking 完全支持 Jina API，共用同一个 key。**\n\n先看一下 OpenViking Docker 部署的配置文件格式：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lhupi2360xl2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/volcengine/OpenViking/main/docs/en/guides/01-configuration.md\" --max-time 10 2>/dev/null | head -200","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":157,"output":196,"cacheRead":80240,"cacheWrite":2178,"totalTokens":82771,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778060815793,"responseId":"064a41102aaea8f76cac00df5821ebb5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4d0f344f","parentId":"b48b2977","timestamp":"2026-05-06T09:47:04.473Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lhupi2360xl2_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Configuration\n\nOpenViking uses a JSON configuration file (`~/.openviking/ov.conf`) for settings.\n\nFor a first-time setup, the recommended flow is:\n\n```bash\nopenviking-server init\nopenviking-server doctor\n```\n\n`openviking-server init` prompts for embedding and VLM settings separately. For API-based VLM choices such as `OpenAI`, `Volcengine`, `Kimi`, and `GLM`, enter the VLM API key when prompted. If you want to use Codex as the VLM provider, choose `OpenAI Codex`; the wizard can import existing Codex auth or guide you through login directly.\n\n## Configuration File\n\nCreate `~/.openviking/ov.conf` in your project directory:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"storage\": {\n    \"workspace\": \"./data\",\n    \"vectordb\": {\n      \"name\": \"context\",\n      \"backend\": \"local\"\n    },\n    \"agfs\": {\n      \"backend\": \"local\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"api_base\" : \"<api-endpoint>\",\n      \"api_key\"  : \"<your-api-key>\",\n      \"provider\" : \"<provider-type>\",\n      \"dimension\": 1024,\n      \"model\"    : \"<model-name>\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"vlm\": {\n    \"api_base\" : \"<api-endpoint>\",\n    \"api_key\"  : \"<your-api-key>\",\n    \"provider\" : \"<provider-type>\",\n    \"model\"    : \"<model-name>\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nFor `provider: \"openai-codex\"`, `vlm.api_key` is optional when Codex OAuth is already available.\n\n## Configuration Examples\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>Volcengine (Doubao Models)</b></summary>\n\n```json\n{\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"api_base\" : \"https://ark.cn-beijing.volces.com/api/v3\",\n      \"api_key\"  : \"your-volcengine-api-key\",\n      \"provider\" : \"volcengine\",\n      \"dimension\": 1024,\n      \"model\"    : \"doubao-embedding-vision-251215\",\n      \"input\": \"multimodal\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"vlm\": {\n    \"api_base\" : \"https://ark.cn-beijing.volces.com/api/v3\",\n    \"api_key\"  : \"your-volcengine-api-key\",\n    \"provider\" : \"volcengine\",\n    \"model\"    : \"doubao-seed-2-0-pro-260215\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>OpenAI Models</b></summary>\n\n```json\n{\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"api_base\" : \"https://api.openai.com/v1\",\n      \"api_key\"  : \"your-openai-api-key\",\n      \"provider\" : \"openai\",\n      \"dimension\": 1536,\n      \"model\"    : \"text-embedding-3-small\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"vlm\": {\n    \"api_base\" : \"https://api.openai.com/v1\",\n    \"api_key\"  : \"your-openai-api-key\",\n    \"provider\" : \"openai\",\n    \"model\"    : \"gpt-5.4\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>Volcengine Embedding + Codex VLM</b></summary>\n\nUse `openviking-server init` to complete the Codex login/import step, then run `openviking-server doctor`.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"api_base\" : \"https://ark.cn-beijing.volces.com/api/v3\",\n      \"api_key\"  : \"your-volcengine-api-key\",\n      \"provider\" : \"volcengine\",\n      \"dimension\": 1024,\n      \"model\"    : \"doubao-embedding-vision-251215\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"vlm\": {\n    \"provider\" : \"openai-codex\",\n    \"model\"    : \"gpt-5.4\",\n    \"api_base\" : \"https://chatgpt.com/backend-api/codex\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>Volcengine Embedding + Kimi Coding VLM</b></summary>\n\n```json\n{\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"api_base\" : \"https://ark.cn-beijing.volces.com/api/v3\",\n      \"api_key\"  : \"your-volcengine-api-key\",\n      \"provider\" : \"volcengine\",\n      \"dimension\": 1024,\n      \"model\"    : \"doubao-embedding-vision-251215\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"vlm\": {\n    \"provider\" : \"kimi\",\n    \"model\"    : \"kimi-code\",\n    \"api_key\"  : \"your-kimi-subscription-api-key\",\n    \"api_base\" : \"https://api.kimi.com/coding\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`kimi` applies the Kimi Coding defaults automatically, including the default Kimi Coding user agent.\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>Volcengine Embedding + GLM Coding Plan VLM</b></summary>\n\n```json\n{\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"api_base\" : \"https://ark.cn-beijing.volces.com/api/v3\",\n      \"api_key\"  : \"your-volcengine-api-key\",\n      \"provider\" : \"volcengine\",\n      \"dimension\": 1024,\n      \"model\"    : \"doubao-embedding-vision-251215\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"vlm\": {\n    \"provider\" : \"glm\",\n    \"model\"    : \"glm-4.6v\",\n    \"api_key\"  : \"your-zai-api-key\",\n    \"api_base\" : \"https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nUse a vision-capable GLM model such as `glm-4.6v` or `glm-5v-turbo` when OpenViking needs image understanding.\n\n</details>\n\n## Configuration Sections\n\n### embedding\n\nEmbedding model configuration for vector search, supporting dense, sparse, and hybrid modes.\n\n#### Dense Embedding\n\n```json\n{\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"max_concurrent\": 10,\n    \"max_retries\": 3,\n    \"text_source\": \"content_only\",\n    \"max_input_tokens\": 4096,\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"provider\": \"volcengine\",\n      \"api_key\": \"your-api-key\","}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1576,"aggregated":"# Configuration\n\nOpenViking uses a JSON configuration file (`~/.openviking/ov.conf`) for settings.\n\nFor a first-time setup, the recommended flow is:\n\n```bash\nopenviking-server init\nopenviking-server doctor\n```\n\n`openviking-server init` prompts for embedding and VLM settings separately. For API-based VLM choices such as `OpenAI`, `Volcengine`, `Kimi`, and `GLM`, enter the VLM API key when prompted. If you want to use Codex as the VLM provider, choose `OpenAI Codex`; the wizard can import existing Codex auth or guide you through login directly.\n\n## Configuration File\n\nCreate `~/.openviking/ov.conf` in your project directory:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"storage\": {\n    \"workspace\": \"./data\",\n    \"vectordb\": {\n      \"name\": \"context\",\n      \"backend\": \"local\"\n    },\n    \"agfs\": {\n      \"backend\": \"local\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"api_base\" : \"<api-endpoint>\",\n      \"api_key\"  : \"<your-api-key>\",\n      \"provider\" : \"<provider-type>\",\n      \"dimension\": 1024,\n      \"model\"    : \"<model-name>\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"vlm\": {\n    \"api_base\" : \"<api-endpoint>\",\n    \"api_key\"  : \"<your-api-key>\",\n    \"provider\" : \"<provider-type>\",\n    \"model\"    : \"<model-name>\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nFor `provider: \"openai-codex\"`, `vlm.api_key` is optional when Codex OAuth is already available.\n\n## Configuration Examples\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>Volcengine (Doubao Models)</b></summary>\n\n```json\n{\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"api_base\" : \"https://ark.cn-beijing.volces.com/api/v3\",\n      \"api_key\"  : \"your-volcengine-api-key\",\n      \"provider\" : \"volcengine\",\n      \"dimension\": 1024,\n      \"model\"    : \"doubao-embedding-vision-251215\",\n      \"input\": \"multimodal\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"vlm\": {\n    \"api_base\" : \"https://ark.cn-beijing.volces.com/api/v3\",\n    \"api_key\"  : \"your-volcengine-api-key\",\n    \"provider\" : \"volcengine\",\n    \"model\"    : \"doubao-seed-2-0-pro-260215\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>OpenAI Models</b></summary>\n\n```json\n{\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"api_base\" : \"https://api.openai.com/v1\",\n      \"api_key\"  : \"your-openai-api-key\",\n      \"provider\" : \"openai\",\n      \"dimension\": 1536,\n      \"model\"    : \"text-embedding-3-small\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"vlm\": {\n    \"api_base\" : \"https://api.openai.com/v1\",\n    \"api_key\"  : \"your-openai-api-key\",\n    \"provider\" : \"openai\",\n    \"model\"    : \"gpt-5.4\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>Volcengine Embedding + Codex VLM</b></summary>\n\nUse `openviking-server init` to complete the Codex login/import step, then run `openviking-server doctor`.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"api_base\" : \"https://ark.cn-beijing.volces.com/api/v3\",\n      \"api_key\"  : \"your-volcengine-api-key\",\n      \"provider\" : \"volcengine\",\n      \"dimension\": 1024,\n      \"model\"    : \"doubao-embedding-vision-251215\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"vlm\": {\n    \"provider\" : \"openai-codex\",\n    \"model\"    : \"gpt-5.4\",\n    \"api_base\" : \"https://chatgpt.com/backend-api/codex\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>Volcengine Embedding + Kimi Coding VLM</b></summary>\n\n```json\n{\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"api_base\" : \"https://ark.cn-beijing.volces.com/api/v3\",\n      \"api_key\"  : \"your-volcengine-api-key\",\n      \"provider\" : \"volcengine\",\n      \"dimension\": 1024,\n      \"model\"    : \"doubao-embedding-vision-251215\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"vlm\": {\n    \"provider\" : \"kimi\",\n    \"model\"    : \"kimi-code\",\n    \"api_key\"  : \"your-kimi-subscription-api-key\",\n    \"api_base\" : \"https://api.kimi.com/coding\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`kimi` applies the Kimi Coding defaults automatically, including the default Kimi Coding user agent.\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary><b>Volcengine Embedding + GLM Coding Plan VLM</b></summary>\n\n```json\n{\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"api_base\" : \"https://ark.cn-beijing.volces.com/api/v3\",\n      \"api_key\"  : \"your-volcengine-api-key\",\n      \"provider\" : \"volcengine\",\n      \"dimension\": 1024,\n      \"model\"    : \"doubao-embedding-vision-251215\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"vlm\": {\n    \"provider\" : \"glm\",\n    \"model\"    : \"glm-4.6v\",\n    \"api_key\"  : \"your-zai-api-key\",\n    \"api_base\" : \"https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nUse a vision-capable GLM model such as `glm-4.6v` or `glm-5v-turbo` when OpenViking needs image understanding.\n\n</details>\n\n## Configuration Sections\n\n### embedding\n\nEmbedding model configuration for vector search, supporting dense, sparse, and hybrid modes.\n\n#### Dense Embedding\n\n```json\n{\n  \"embedding\": {\n    \"max_concurrent\": 10,\n    \"max_retries\": 3,\n    \"text_source\": \"content_only\",\n    \"max_input_tokens\": 4096,\n    \"dense\": {\n      \"provider\": \"volcengine\",\n      \"api_key\": \"your-api-key\",","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778060824472}}
