{"type":"message","id":"121ce1e3","parentId":"71096a9d","timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:52:35.992Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try a different approach - maybe the file_name \"evolver\" is actually a doc token. Let me check if there's a feishu doc associated with it.Actually, the user said the file_name is \"evolver\" - this might mean it's a file uploaded to Feishu that I can download. But the drive:file scope isn't enabled.\n\nWait - the user said \"我发给你的是skill\" - they sent me a SKILL. This could mean they uploaded a skill file through the Feishu chat. Let me check if there's a recent media file in the inbound directory that I haven't processed yet.Actually, I need to re-read the conversation. The user sent a message with `[media reference removed - already processed by model]` earlier, and then later sent `{\"file_key\":\"file_v3_0111e_45552b13-77db-4292-b08a-e0cc660d72ag\",\"file_name\":\"evolver\"}`.\n\n\nSo they did send a file - the file_key \"file_v3_0111e_45552b13-77db-4292-b08a-e0cc660d72ag\" with filename \"evolver\". I attempted to download it via the drive API but hit a permission error on the drive:file:download scope. Let me try using the feishu_doc tool to access it instead, though I don't have a doc_token from this file_key.\n\nActually, maybe I should check if this file is accessible through the IM message media API rather than the drive API. Let me look at recent media files in the inbound directory to see if there's another way to retrieve this.","thinkingSignature":"8d2cdc3fe0eddfc1b89cf078a2ba9c584c5822bca0d0fff1ab3d16596848c431"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_crh8vi75xlfu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -lt /home/halei/.openclaw/media/inbound/ 2>/dev/null | head -10","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":72684,"output":401,"cacheRead":22067,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95152,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRe