{"type":"message","id":"2b229707","parentId":"c5e7d68d","timestamp":"2026-05-06T12:52:48.793Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's no recent evolver file. The file was sent through Feishu's file system, not as a media upload in the chat. The `file_key` format suggests it's a Feishu Drive file. Without the `drive:file:download` permission, I can't download it.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe the user sent the SKILL content as text in the chat? But I don't see any text content from them about the skill.\n\nActually, re-reading the message: \"我发给你的是skill，安装这个skil 启动这个项目\" - they sent me a SKILL. Maybe they sent it as a Feishu document and expect me to read it via feishu_doc. But I need the doc_token, not file_key.\n \nOh, I see the issue now - the file_key might actually be a doc_token in disguise. Feishu doc URLs follow a pattern like `https://xxx.feishu.cn/docx/ABC123def`, so the part after `/docx/` would be the token. But the user gave me `file_v3_0111e_45552b13-77db-4292-b08a-e0cc660d72ag`, which looks like a file_key rather than a doc_token, so I'm not sure if I can use it with the docx endpoint.\n\nThe file_name \"evolver\" with no extension makes me think this might be a raw text or markdown file rather than a proper document. The real blocker is that the feishu app needs the `drive:file:download` permission to access files this way, so I should ask the user to either enable that permission or share the file differently.","thinkingSignature":"92e335ad2325e9bd4321debe2219c029213d06c59f814fd284f3e113d414a2dc"},{"type":"text","text":"**读不到文件**，因为飞书应用没有 `drive:file:download` 权限。\n\n两个办法：\n\n**方案 1（推荐）：开通权限**\n在飞书开放平台给 `cli_a93650c6fc785bce` 添加 `drive:file` 权限，我就能直接读。\n\n**方案 2：直接发 SKILL.md 的内容**\n你把 `capability-evolver/SKILL.md` 的内容复制粘贴发给我就行，不需要下载文件。\n\n---\n\n你想用哪个方案？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":73430,"output":456,"cacheRead":22067,"cacheWrite":0,"t